# HeroUI v3 Component System

When working on frontend UI or component code, use HeroUI v3 as the required component system.

- Use `@heroui/react` v3 components for interactive UI primitives such as buttons, cards, forms, inputs, modals, popovers, tabs, chips, tooltips, menus, and scroll areas.
- Do not introduce another component library for UI primitives unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Do not hand-roll primitives that already exist in HeroUI v3. Compose and style HeroUI components instead.
- Use Tailwind/CSS for layout, spacing, visual treatment, and project-specific art direction, but keep behavior, accessibility, and component semantics on HeroUI v3 primitives.
- Prefer local wrappers only when they standardize repeated project patterns around HeroUI v3 components.
- Import HeroUI components from `@heroui/react`.

Example:

```tsx
import { Button, Card, Input } from "@heroui/react";
```

## Animate UI Exception (Motion-Only)

Per ADR 0002, [Animate UI](https://animate-ui.com/) is allowed as a motion
layer only, never as a component library.

- Animate UI source may live only in `src/shared/ui/motion/**` (motion effect
  atoms) or `src/shared/ui/icons/animated/**` (animated Lucide icons).
- Do not port Animate UI's Button, Card, Input, Dialog, Tabs, Tooltip,
  Popover, Accordion, Dropdown, Select, Checkbox, Switch, Badge, Avatar,
  Skeleton, Spinner, or any other component-category asset. HeroUI v3
  covers all of these.
- Do not port Animate UI's Radix / Base UI / Headless UI primitive wrappers.
  Use HeroUI primitives backed by React Aria instead.
- Motion atoms must wrap HeroUI components, not replace them. Example: put
  a `BlurFade` around a HeroUI `Card`; do not swap the `Card` for a
  shadcn-style card.
- The only animation runtime dependency is `motion`. Do not import
  `motion/react` outside `src/shared/ui/motion/**` or
  `src/shared/ui/icons/animated/**`.
- Motion atoms must honor `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` and render a
  static fallback when motion is reduced.
- Colors and easings inside motion atoms must consume `--muse-*` tokens and
  `--muse-ease-*` curves (see `muse-design-system.mdc`). Do not inline shadcn
  CSS variables.
- Each ported file needs a short top-of-file header declaring its Animate UI
  upstream source (component name and commit hash or version), to keep diffs
  reviewable.
